detail.title: Reduce inflation by removing base and bonus proposer rewards
detail.description:
We propose to reduce inflation by reducing base and bonus proposer rewards to 0 and increase the community tax by this amount. Delegator rewards will **NOT** be affected as this only changes
the extra reward a validator gets for proposing a block. Validator commision will **NOT** be affected as the validator regardless of the proposer rewards always gets a commission. Making the base and bonus proposer rewards
to 0 and the community tax to 7% we have an effective reduction of 5% inflation **WITHOUT REDUCING THE APR/APY FOR STAKERS**.
Community pool tokens are locked up and can **ONLY** be unlocked by a governance proposal


Vote YES if you agree with removing proposer rewards
Vote NO if you disagree with removing proposer rewards
Vote ABSTAIN if you refrain from voting
Vote NO WITH VETO if you see this proposal as harmful or spam

[Commonwealth Thread](https://commonwealth.im/sentinel/discussion/13492-proposal-39-inflation-reduction-by-removing-base-and-bonus-proposer-rewards).

detail.title: Establish Growth Dao for Sentinel
detail.description:
I propose the establishment of a growth dao to manage the community fund and take the lead on various campaigns including, but not limited to: 
Governance structure
Community engagement from a community perspective
Wite-label dvpn development
Funding, Marketing and Partnerships
Research and development

Full proposal can be read [here](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1XZXl5utodSm48gXwsi2PDlVocpiChFois_N1Q__mWlc).

**Funding**
I propose a funding allocation from the community treasury of 250 million $dvpn tokens, for the execution of these initiatives. The exact amount will be determined based on the needs and scale of our operations and will be subject to approval by the dao members. A multi-sig wallet has been created and will be maintained by dao members and advisors. 

multisig wallet: **sent1ug9ene2fkw749nutuzd858r6sqeljt6f6vya33**
The signers are : seventh, joey badgerbite , trinity validator , bart chainvibes and sergey quokka stake


**Dao communication channel:[https://t.Me/sentinelgrowthdao](https://t.Me/sentinelgrowthdao)

vote yes if you support the creation of the Growth Dao and the contents of the proposal. 
vote no if you think that the Growth Dao should not be established and reject the contents of the proposal. 
vote abstain if you do not have a strong opinion on the subject.
vote no with veto if you think this proposal is harming the network and the depositors should be slashed for submitting it.

Thanks for reading the [proposal](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1XZXl5utodSm48gXwsi2PDlVocpiChFois_N1Q__mWlc), 
seventh​

detail.title: Sentinel Hub Software Upgrade - 5
detail.description:
This is a Software Upgrade proposal to upgrade the Sentinel Hub software from version v0.10.x to v0.11.x, incorporating the following notable improvements:

- Upgrade Cosmos SDK to v0.45.16.
- Upgrade Cosmos IBC to v4.4.2.
- Upgrade CosmWasm to v0.31.0.
- Replace Tendermint Core with CometBFT v0.34.27.
- Introduce time-based node subscriptions.
- Implement hourly payouts for nodes.
- Share the plan-based subscription bandwidth with others.
- Enhance blockchain queries.
- Include other minor fixes and improvements.

If this proposal is approved, the Blockchain will stop producing blocks at height 12,310,005, which is expected to occur on August 18, 2023, at 01:00 PM UTC. All validators are required to coordinate within the Sentinel Validators' group and restart their validator nodes with the specified version at the specified block height.

detail.title: Implementing a Tiered Governance Discussion Period
detail.description:
During my focus on changing the economic model (a separate proposal is coming), it occurred that we should look at the governance model as well.  I've identified the need for a more nuanced approach to managing different types of proposals. I understand that different categories of proposals require varying degrees of scrutiny and pace, and with this in mind, I propose the following tiered governance procedure. 

"Normal" Proposals: I suggest keeping the existing process for normal proposals, including a 7-day discussion period on Commonwealth and a 7-day on-chain voting period.

Description: Normal - any non-network upgrade that can be applied via governance parameters or allotment of community funds to fund projects

"Fast" Technical Proposals: For technical proposals, which are often more urgent and less controversial, I propose a shorter 4-day discussion period on Commonwealth. After this, the proposal will be subject to a 7-day on-chain voting period.

Technical - any network upgrade or software implementation that requires all validators to participate or drastic changes to the DVPN node software that would require many people to update their nodes or any DEX funding listings on new chains.

"Emergency" Proposals: For matters of immediate concern that necessitate swift action, I propose that these emergency proposals skip the Commonwealth discussion period and proceed directly to on-chain voting. Ideally, I would label these proposals as 'Emergency' on the chain, and they would be subject to a 1-day on-chain voting period.

Emergency - any security-related threat or chain-breaking code that needs updating

For all types of proposals, We should all link discussions posted on Commonwealth to the Sentinel social channels (Telegram, Discord etc) within 1-2 hours, except for Emergency Proposals that bypass Commonwealth. This is to ensure that I maintain transparency and engage as many stakeholders as possible in the decision-making process.

In the future, we can always review this proposal depending on how busy the chain becomes in terms of governance props being issued. 

To vote on my proposal:
Vote YES if you support the implementation of the tiered proposal discussion period.
Vote NO if you think the current governance model should stay.
Vote ABSTAIN if you don't hold a strong opinion on the matter.
Vote NO WITH VETO if you believe this amendment could harm the network, and the depositors should be penalized for submitting it.

detail.title: Inflation adjustment proposal - 3
detail.description:
After several community voting procedures, it has been inferred that the ideal rate for inflation as proposed by the majority is a target of 15%. This proposal aims to amend the current max inflation rate from 37% to 15%, the min inflation rate from 25% to 12%, and the rate of inflation change to 3%. This trend of inflation reduction has been prevalent in the Cosmos ecosystem and a good reference would be the inflation rate reduction of the Akash network that happened earlier this year.

Vote YES if you agree that inflation should be reduced.
Vote NO if you don't want this inflation reduction.
Vote ABSTAIN if you forfeit your vote.
Vote NO WITH VETO if you see this proposal as spam/harmful.

detail.title: Reducing on-chain governance time
detail.description:
the BlueFrenDAO, led by @Grandmasterbepe and @joey19944 from Badgerbite brings forward this proposal.

Our goal is to streamline governance and hasten the voting process for proposals on the chain.
Currently, the 7-day discussion period before a proposal is put on chain adds 7 days to the overall voting period, resulting in a total of 21 days.

We propose to decrease the on-chain voting time from 14 to 7 days, bringing the total back to the standard 14-day period. This change is imperative for reasons such as node pricing, community-driven initiatives, and the ability to seize new opportunities as a community.

Voting YES signifies support for reducing the on-chain voting time by 7 days.
Voting NO opposes the proposal.
ABSTAIN indicates no strong opinion on the proposal.
NO WITH VETO signifies that the proposal is seen as harmful or spam. Commonwealth discussion : https://commonwealth.im/sentinel/discussion/9907-reducing-onchain-governance-time

detail.title: Periodic price adjustment for node bandwidth pricing - 2
detail.description:
Most cVPNs I see charge 10$/month unless you commit to 12/24 month plans. The average internet user apparently consumes 500gb/month, which I will use for price calculation. Since we don't have subscriptions yet we have to go by consumption.
With a DVPN price of ~0.00075$, I propose to charge 11dvpn/gb (or 0.008$/gb) which is equal to a 4$/month subscription to a cVPN using the above metrics of data consumption. This means we still undercut all centralized VPN providers by a long shot while also increasing buy pressure from consumers. Even when the DVPN price rises we still have some head room to stay competitive.
 In addition I propose that node providers should have the ability to charge as much as they want for the service they provide. Since it seems like the parameter can't stay empty the maximal price is set to 7000dvpn/gb (or ~5$/gb)
Decentre, Atom, Osmosis and Secret prices are all adjusted to 0.008$/gb as well.

For the following part I want to differentiate between adjustments and price changes.
An adjustment means we change the DVPN value in order to match the price of 0.008$/gb in case the DVPN price increases or decreases.
For example: we charge 11dvpn/gb but the DVPN price rises to 0.001$. In order to keep the same price point we have to adjust the amount of DVPN charged to 8dvpn/gb.

A price change would mean that the community is not happy with the price point of 11dvpn/gb (or 0.008$/gb) anymore and wants to increase or decrease the price.
For example: we charge 11dvpn/gb the DVPN price stays at 0.00075$ but we realize that this price point is too steep to attract new customers. In order to do this we change the price to 4dvpn/gb equal to ~0.003$/gb.

In order to be flexible with adjustments in reaction to price fluctuations of DVPN, I propose that we set aside the need for a 7 day commonwealth discussion phase before bringing an adjustment proposal on chain and change the required discussion time to 1 day. For price changes there will still be the need for a commonwealth thread where the proposer elaborates on why he wants to change the price and takes input from the community for 7 days.


Vote YES if you agree with the price of 11dvpn/gb (~0.008$/gb) and the lowering of the discussion period for adjustments to 1 day
Vote NO if you disagree with either the min price or the changes of rules in regards of the discussion period for adjustments
Vote ABSTAIN if you refrain from voting
Vote NO WITH VETO if you see this proposal as harmful or spam

**Commonwealth Thread**
https://commonwealth.im/sentinel/discussion/9585-setting-a-minimum-node-price

detail.title: Listing DVPN on KUJIRA EMERGENCY PROPOSAL
detail.description:
We are respectfully requesting your support in making this proposal an emergency one. Given the rapidly changing dynamics of the current market and the growing interest in Sentinel, we believe it is crucial to act swiftly and decisively. The current 7-day discussion period and 14-day governance cycle may not be sufficient to stay ahead of emerging trends and community-led initiatives.

Therefore, we propose launching this proposal on the chain after only 48 hours of discussion, in order to seize the moment and ensure our collective success. We are confident that with your support, we can make this proposal a reality and drive meaningful progress towards our shared goals.

The BlueFrenDAO, led by @Grandmasterbepe and @joey19944 from Badgerbite, is proposing to list dVPN on the Kujuri platform. In order to achieve this goal, the BlueFrenDao team is requesting funding for the following items:

10,000 Kuji tokens to post a proposal for a dVPN listing vote. This would cost 8.125.000 dVPN, which will be returned to the community fund if the vote is successful.

Server setup and maintenance costs for two full nodes for a period of one year. The estimated monthly cost of the server and monitoring is $100 which amounts to a total of $1200 or 1.250.000 dVPN.

In total, the BlueFrenDao is requesting 10,000,000 DVPN to list dVPN on Kujira. The funds will be managed by BlueFrenDAO and will be paid into the wallet sent1d09kk5rrrf0vsf9jr3rsl3c7qmty2shd8elt2h.

We feel it's the moment to levarage the incredible platform of Kujira and believe it will give more exposure and buy pressure to the sentinel dvpn token. Kujira is a decentralized platform that offers different kind of products including a permissionless orderbook. Commonwealth discussion : https://commonwealth.im/sentinel/discussion/9944-listing-dvpn-on-kujira-emergency-proposal

Therefore, we propose launching this proposal on the chain after only 48 hours of discussion, in order to seize the moment and ensure our collective success. We are confident that with your support, we can make this proposal a reality and drive meaningful progress towards our shared goals.

The BlueFrenDAO, led by @Grandmasterbepe and @joey19944 from Badgerbite, is proposing to list dVPN on the Kujuri platform. In order to achieve this goal, the BlueFrenDao team is requesting funding for the following items:

10,000 Kuji tokens to post a proposal for a dVPN listing vote. This would cost 8.125.000 dVPN, which will be returned to the community fund if the vote is successful.

Server setup and maintenance costs for two full nodes for a period of one year. The estimated monthly cost of the server and monitoring is $100 which amounts to a total of $1200 or 1.250.000 dVPN.

In total, the BlueFrenDao is requesting 10,000,000 DVPN to list dVPN on Kujira. The funds will be managed by BlueFrenDAO and will be paid into the wallet sent1d09kk5rrrf0vsf9jr3rsl3c7qmty2shd8elt2h.

We feel it's the moment to levarage the incredible platform of Kujira and believe it will give more exposure and buy pressure to the sentinel dvpn token. Kujira is a decentralized platform that offers different kind of products including a permissionless orderbook. detail.title: Use of Community tokens to fund V2Ray Sentinel nodes deployed on the Akash Network.
detail.description:
Together with Joey, we are proposing the allocation of $2000 USD (5,864,586.69) $dVPN at the time of writing) from the Sentinel Community Fund to fund the development of V2Ray nodes deployed on the Akash Network. This project work will be carried out by @dimokus, a highly skilled and experienced developer on the Akash network.

With this proposal, we aim to provide secure and scalable infrastructure for the deployment of decentralized VPN applications. By integrating v2Ray nodes, the network will offer an additional layer of privacy and security to users, making it an even more attractive proposition in an ever-growing and competitive market. This is evident in the Chinese market, the world's largest for VPNs; this proposal is a small part in the journey of attempting to capture some of that valuable market share.

Payment to the developer will be made on delivery, ensuring that the funds are utilized efficiently and effectively. Additionally, all transactions related to the project will be published and open for audit, providing transparency and accountability to the Community.

The wallet that will receive these funds will be managed by The BlueFrenDAO, which represents our first true test towards the community.

Wallet address for funds: sent1up98v3pexk5l0l0vmn485rxdedkqae6pmrkh8k
This funding is based on the following quotes :  50 hours of work at a rate of 30$ /hour.
$1500 in total. We are requesting an additional $500 to account for fluctuations in the wider market. Once payment is settled, any surplus tokens will be sent back to the community fund.

The work performed will include both the implementation itself and guides in Russian and English.
With this implementation, users will be able to use the cloudmos deploy tool to select the dVPN template and deploy nodes with a few clicks of the mouse buttons on a decentralized platform.

As chief fren of The BlueFrenDAO, I understand the importance of transparency and trust, and I am confident that this proposal will receive the support of the Community. I believe that this initiative will not only benefit the Sentinel Network but will also increase awareness of the BlueFrenDAO and its commitment to innovation and growth. Cough cough, and our upcoming NFT set to be released.

Thank you for considering this proposal. We look forward to your support and to working together to reclaim Sentinel's rightful place among the Cosmos.

Grandmaster Bepe & Joey

By voting YES, you agree for the funding to be released and work to begin deploying V2Ray nodes through Akash.
By voting NO, you disagree with the proposal.
By voting ABSTAIN, you refrain from voting.
By voting NO WITH VETO, you see this proposal as harmful or spam

detail.title: Periodic price adjustment for node bandwidth pricing - 1
detail.description: With the new upgrade, Sentinel Hub can now set a floor and ceiling price for dVPN nodes' bandwidth, our goal as a network should be to set the best price at which the highest amount of nodes are profitable while retaining competitiveness and being the cheapest VPN provider on the market. These prices should be re-evaluated frequently by white-labels and node providers to keep the service competitive.

detail.title: Sentinel Hub Software Upgrade - 4
detail.description:
This is the follow-up proposal which implements the changes agreed on in the signaling proposal passed on the 9th of October ( https://www.mintscan.io/sentinel/proposals/13 ) for a Software Upgrade to update the Sentinel Hub software to version v0.10.x (latest) with the following improvements:

- CosmWasm integration
- Inflation reduction to 25%
- dVPN nodes tax module
- Minimum pricing for dVPN nodes
- Staking contracts

The discussion of this proposal can be found here:
https://commonwealth.im/sentinel/discussion/6782-sentinel-next-upgrade

If this proposal passes the Blockchain will stop producing the blocks at the height [9,348,475](https://www.mintscan.io/sentinel/blocks/9348475) which is expected to happen on 27th January 2023, 12:00 PM UTC. All the validators should coordinate on Sentinel Validators' group and restart the validator node with the specified version at the specified block height.

detail.title: Inflation adjustment proposal
detail.description:
As previously discussed, the next scheduled inflation reduction was supposed to merge the two yearly inflation drops into one, so instead of having a 6% drop in September, a 12% drop to 25% was promised. The standard 6-monthly 6% drop happened in September automatically via the inflation module. So the inflation right now sits at 31%. The additional 6% drop to get to 25% inflation is still missing and will be implemented with the passing of this proposal.

Vote YES if you agree that the inflation should be reduced to 25% as planned

detail.title: Publish a detailed token release schedule and increase transparency
detail.description:
The team claims in the following statement responding to the recent controversy on Twitter about the Sentinel Foundation treasury wallet, that the “Tokens lock-up schedules are clearly listed“ and that “there is clear transparency“ when it comes to tracking those token unlocks.

“In early 2021, the Sentinel network made a transition from an ERC20 token to its own Cosmos hub and there was a tokenomics update made to ensure sustenance of community development and all of its other stakeholders. If we see most networks today whether on Cosmos or on other networks have a distribution of over 40-50% at the minimum ranging upwards to 70% of tokens being allocated for community and development organizations/marketing. Tokens lock-up schedules are clearly listed, and there is transparency in these processes of the movement of tokens. Generally, in most networks these token amounts are split up into several wallets and not all networks indicate or label all of the wallets. In Sentinel there is clear transparency, as the unlocks and the wallet balance can be traced back to one wallet that is visible on-chain to the community.“
- ProjectAutonomy

Further ProjectAutonomy suggested that community members with questions about tokenomics, and the reasoning behind them, consult [this Medium article](https://medium.com/sentinel/sentinels-next-chapter-the-path-to-dvpn-mass-adoption-5d8a0b2afaba)

When looking into this article all we are presented with is [this image](https://miro.medium.com/max/4800/1*K8_H3IInYfpJ_CQPpJbOSg.png). So the “clearly listed“ lock-up schedules are [this](https://imgur.com/a/g9krefc). It is anything but “clearly listed“ and needs further, more detailed formulation.

The wish for exactly that was made for example [here](https://t.me/sentinel_co/288772), in direct DM with admins nearly 3 months ago without success or a more [recent effort](https://t.me/SentinelGov/4697) also without success.

With the most recent reference to the not so clear article and the repeated ignoring for a more detailed release schedule we can assume that the team has no interested in publishing one and wants to leave us in the dark.


Onwards to the mentioned “transparency in these processes of the movement of tokens.“

This is the Sentinel Foundation wallet and these are the wallets that received Dvpn from the Foundation wallet:

Directly received funds:
sent1u9szkhxh6ezhd7vp0prcfjx7vsyn3jup75xtf2
sent1skt2ja3m7w2d7nldvq6fsdlj3hgzkk0uhk6t0h

All staking reward addresses:
sent1jyae2x9vdf9d6cs3qx0qatrqxfvkunjm6jglv0 started selling recently
sent1djhzx3xzqct47dyfpkh4r8etvvvd0nvtsfse8p
sent1dlvexscz0gttgmgqxpx7edlh86nm692sc699yu proposal deposit funds, outgoing to random address/ validator address
sent1lh59pphtxe4ch7jslpmv9ps354jdm7u2f87x44
sent1whe0gv3qtc07fm2wvun7mk2f9fy08pmasehpk6 outgoing, partly sold, send to validator address
sent107um8pcshwgnm6ramfl376n9p7pcxmxqjeesk8 partly send to osmosis pools
sent1csyt9f96dlqvyjtyze9z4fmp5vru6hftl92asl alot send to Ascendex after just being listed, Osmos and random wallets
sent1hmcnmtecmem3z9r3ssk2w6zsgth3dfdu8u6258 270mil to send out
sent1ehuvq87lfn7cqwv5cet2lx6jp5q0symgk0xq8s
sent1hmpx067hnuzhf8rjsdmtcgf92h4f099sme9czz same as above also send to Ascendex/Mexc
sent13f7jk6dqz7hsthhvxy0jhfyhv4zjfef7svc4lp holds a lot, parts sold, part send for node incentives

Just as mentioned in text the Sentinel network does not differ from the many other networks since the funds are just the same “split up into several wallets and not all networks indicate or label all of the wallets.“

For some wallets you can assume their purpose after digging very deep and going through a lot of transactions and wallets. But just because you can track funds back to one wallet you can't call it transparency. There is no way to know who has control of the above funds and the wallets/ the wallets funds were forwarded to. There is no way to know why certain wallets got payed by foundation controlled wallets. There is no way to know what the funds were/ are going to be used for. And there is also no way to know when they unlock.

**To make it clearer when and how many tokens are unlocked we want to see a more detailed release schedule. For real transparency we want to know where the funds meant for advisors, validator incentives, node host incentives, ecosystem partners, marketing, treasury, team and offerings end up/are located at this time.**
To give the team sufficient time, those information shall be released 30 days after this proposal has passed.


Vote YES if you agree that the team shall release above information
Vote NO if you don't want the team to release above information
Vote ABSTAIN if you forfeit your vote
Vote NO WITH VETO if you see this proposal as spam/harmful

**Commonwealth Thread**
https://commonwealth.im/sentinel/discussion/7502-publish-a-detailed-token-release-schedule-and-increase-transparency

detail.title: Staking contract proposal - 5 years duration
detail.description:
By voting YES on this staking contract proposal you will lock your entire token balance (through non-removable vesting accounts) in exchange for a DVPN bonus.

Once the vesting account is put in place the action cannot be undone.

- 5 years lock duration plus 18 months vesting for 1.18x the DVPN tokens. As an example, if you lock 100 tokens you will receive an additional 18 DVPN tokens
- The additional tokens are locked inside the vesting account too
- After 5 years or 1826.25 days, the tokens will be linearly unlocked over a period of 18 months

The DVPN balance of all the people who voted YES will be updated during the next chain upgrade.

This proposal is a follow-up to [proposal 13](https://www.mintscan.io/sentinel/proposals/13), which was approved on 2022-10-09.

Voting NO or ABSTAIN has no effect, if you voted YES but change your mind you can vote NO or ABSTAIN before the voting ends and you won't be included in the staking contract, in case you vote YES on multiple staking contracts only the shortest will be considered valid.

detail.title: Establishing governance procedure on Sentinel
detail.description:
Several other blockchains have adopted governance procedure and sentinel shouldn’t be the exception. It allows for good discussions from all parties that have interests in the Sentinel chain

A precedent be created that a given period of discussion (*7 days* min.) for any on-chain proposals take place on Commonwealth. detail.title: SIP-10: Inflation reduction to promote sustainability
detail.description:
We propose to decrease the inflation from **37%** to **23%** at the time of writing. Currently the inflation is too high and not substainable for long term network growth.
The new inflation model can be found here : [https://i.postimg.cc/pd4JhBvt/inflation.jpg/](https://i.postimg.cc/pd4JhBvt/inflation.jpg)
Discussion about this inflation model can be read here [https://t.me/SentinelGov/2508](https://t.me/SentinelGov/2508)
The curve will meet the same exact point after a duration so there is no impact for long term holders.

*Vote YES if you think the inflation should be reduced to 23%.

*Vote NO if you think the inflation shouldn't be reduced.

*Vote ABSTAIN if you don't have a strong opinion about the subject.

*Vote NO WITH VETO if you think this proposal is harming the network and the depositor should be slashed for submitting it.

detail.description:

- Upgrade Cosmos SDK to v0.44.x
- Upgrade Cosmos IBC to v2.x.x
- Upgrage Tendermint Core to v0.34.x
- Query improvements
- Remove unnecessary data storage from the subscription, session KV stores

detail.title: Change of vesting unlock timeline
detail.description:
To favor the success of upcoming releases and the tier-1 exchange listing, the unlock schedule of the team's and investors' vesting accounts will be adjusted and postponed by exactly 3 months 5 days.

Accounts of normal users and delegators will not be impacted by this vesting delay, this only concerns team, and private investors' tokens.

If this proposal passes Sentinel team will make specified modifications in the Sentinel Hub Software Upgrade - 2.

detail.title: Inflation parameter changes according to Sentinel token economics model
detail.description:
Sentinel planned token economics model was published before mainnet launch, in the publication it explained the periodical decrease to the annual inflation rate by 6% for every 6 months until it reaches 13% since the mainnet launch date. If this proposal passes, the Sentinel Hub Software Upgrade - 2 will apply the following changes by introducing a custom mint module.

Current values:
Max inflation rate: 55%
Min inflation rate: 49%

New values:
Max inflation rate: 49%
Min inflation rate: 43%

detail.title: Sentinel Hub Software Upgrade - 1
detail.description: Sentinel Hub recently when through a hard-fork upgrade where the Blockchain state was migrated from Cosmos SDK v0.39.2. The current version of Sentinel Hub is running with Cosmos SDK v0.42.5 which has a lot of features including IBC, Quick state sync, etc. Although the upgrade was smooth and successful we found out there is one issue with multi-signature accounts. The migration scripts partially migrated the public keys of the multi-signature accounts making them unable to make transactions. To fix this issue we are planning to have a soft-fork upgrade at block height 1,272,000 which is expected to happen on ~24-06-2021 at 12:00:00 UTC. The upgrade guide will be available for all the validators on Sentinel's official GitHub repository. This issue did not affect any other accounts, funds, or the consensus layer of the chain.
